annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L13; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL13 family
annotationB: Nascent polypeptide-associated complex subunit alpha; May promote appropriate targeting of ribosome-nascent polypeptide complexes (By similarity). Required for correct localization of the osk/oskar protein to the posterior pole during embryonic development. The osk protein directs the recruitment of molecules responsible for posterior body patterning and germline formation in the embryo
